94. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2019601734
T1  - PREDICTION OF OOCYTE QUALITY THROUGH MEASUREMENT OF LEUKAEMIA INHIBITORY FACTOR LEVEL IN THE SERUM AND FOLLICULAR FLUID OF PCOS WOMEN AND NON-PCOS UNDERGOING IVF/ICSI CYCLE IN SAMPLES OF IRAQI WOMEN
A1  - Khalial G.M.
A1  - Al-Dujaily S.S.
A1  - Al-Jubory W.A. 
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Leukaemia inhibitory factor (LIF) is a cytokine that belongs to the interleukin-6 family of cytokines and is a key regulates of estrogenic activity. Human LIF may help increase the implantation rate in women with unexplained infertility. To predict oocyte quality and maturation earlier through measurement of LIF level in the serum and follicular fluid during the preovulatry stage of PCOS and non-PCOS women undergoing an IVF/ICSI cycle. Fifty infertile couples, 25 with PCOS and 25 without PCOS, attended the High Institute of Infertility Diagnosis and Assisted Reproductive Technologies at Al-Nahrain University in Baghdad, Iraq, for the study. The females that participated were between the ages of 18 - 40 years). LIF level measures in serum and follicular fluid at day of oocyte pick up. ICSI was performed and embryo transfer (ET) was done for all women. Comparison of the biomarker between PCOS and non PCOS showed a highly significant (p < 0.001) differences in the level of LIF that measured in the serum (LIF=798 +/- 33.85) and follicular fluid (LIF=415 +/- 26.10) of PCOS women compared to non-PCOS women serum (LIF=183 +/-7.13) and follicular fluid (LIF=196 +/- 7.85), respectively. The mean of total oocytes number and MII oocytes was significantly higher in PCOS compared to non-PCOS women. However, oocytes characteristics were shown no significant differences between PCOS and non-PCOS women. LIF level in the serum and follicular fluid was higher at the time of oocyte retrieval, in PCOS women as compared with non PCOS women. The mean of oocytes characteristics was similar between PCOS and non-PCOS groups. Therefore, LIF cannot be used as biomarker for oocyte quality and maturation in PCOS women.Copyright © 2022. Biochemical and Cellular Archives. All Rights Reserved.
