T1  - Oophorectomy for fertility preservation
A1  - Hartigan L.
A1  - Broderick V.
A1  - Cullinane J.
A1  - Glover L.
A1  - Martyn F.
A1  - Wingfield M. 
Y1  - 2020//
N2  - Presentation Turner syndrome (TS) is the most established genetic cause of premature ovarian insufficiency (POI). A 14-year-old girl with a TS mosaic karyotype was referred to the adolescent gynaecology department to discuss fertility preservation (FP) options. Diagnosis We report the first case of oophorectomy for the purpose of ovarian tissue cryopreservation (OTC) performed in Ireland. Treatment Oophorectomy was performed in Dublin and the ovary was transported to Oxford for cryopreservation. Conclusion OTC to preserve fertility is still considered experimental but is offered as a clinical service in other countries. Until now this technique has not been available in Ireland. It is the authors' hope that a FP service can be developed in Ireland.Copyright © 2020, Irish Medical Association. All rights reserved.
